# 📅 Week 0 – Environment Setup & Tool Installation

## 🎯 Objectives
- Install and configure the required open-source EDA tools.
- Verify basic functionality of each tool.
- Document the installation process with logs/screenshots.

---

## 🛠️ Tools Installed
- **Icarus Verilog (iverilog)** → Verilog simulator  
- **GTKWave** → Waveform viewer  
- **Yosys** → Logic synthesis  
- **OpenLane (Docker method)** → RTL-to-GDSII flow  
- **SkyWater 130nm PDK** (checked via container / optional local clone)

---

## ✅ Steps Followed
1. Installed prerequisites (`docker`, `git`, `make`, `python3`).
2. Cloned the repository and initialized submodules:
   ```bash
   git clone --recurse-submodules https://github.com/<your-username>/openlane-setup-myflow.git
   cd openlane-setup-myflow
